title: Tathra Australian Football Club
description: Our Club was established in 1983 and is based at Lawrence Park  Tathra. We are a  family focused football Club with a goal of making Aussie rules football  available accessible to all children  youth and adults of both genders.     Aussie rules football is a great game to play as it captures the best of other  football codes and requires a mixture of stamina  strength and ball skills. It s  fun to learn and there is always opportunity to improve one s skills.    Importantly we we want all our players  members  volunteers  committee members  to feel welcome. On the ground we want all our players to be respectful of all  others and off the ground we encourage all players  members  volunteers to be  part of the social activities that we have as part of each season and volunteer  some time where possible.    For kids we have regular social events and KicknChips on Thursday night after  training.
openinghours: Season starts April thru to September each year

title: Bega Valley Archers
description: From 9am   first  third and fifth Saturdays of the month    Bega Valley Archers is a club that caters to the sport of archery. Club  activities focus is on traditional forms of archery  Asian archery and Olympic  styles of archery.    The club meets at from 9 am on the first  third and fifth Saturdays of the month  at Colombo Park Bemboka. The activities usually conclude around 2 pm.    The club provides all archery and safety gear and caters for archers from the  age of 8 with parent or guardian attending.    For further information contact Venke Mannes  President Bega Valley Archers.

title: Bega Valley Motorcycle Expo
description: Bega Valley Motorcycle Expo is a Community focused not for profit organisation  designed around celebrating all forms of Motorcycling activity around the Bega  Valley   surrounding regions.    The Expo promotes local   surrounding motorcycle related business s   groups    sporting organisations  tourism operaters   establishments.    The Bega Valley Motorcycle Expo supports numerous Community Organisations   including the Childrens ward at South East Regional Hospital   Candeelo Public  School.    The Bega Valley Motorcycle Expo is held annuanly on the 1st Saturday in  September at Bega Showgrounds.
